♪

01:38.798 --> 01:40.166
Home sweet home.

01:41.868 --> 01:43.770
We'll try and make it fun.

01:43.803 --> 01:45.305
Stop lying to me.

01:46.639 --> 01:48.408
Never seen you
scared before.

01:49.375 --> 01:50.443
I'm not scared, sweetie.

01:50.477 --> 01:51.744
Let's go.

01:52.378 --> 01:54.147
Come on, move it.

01:55.982 --> 01:57.851
(TV background noise)

01:57.884 --> 01:59.185
Vance.

01:59.219 --> 02:00.186
Vance:
Morning, Taj.

02:00.220 --> 02:01.321
All right, lock everything up.

02:01.354 --> 02:02.288
Send everyone home, all right.

02:02.322 --> 02:03.323
Get to the security station.

02:03.356 --> 02:04.324
Mena, stay with Vance.

02:04.357 --> 02:05.859
I'll be back in a minute.

02:06.359 --> 02:07.594
All right, let's go!

02:07.627 --> 02:09.162
Lock it all down!

02:14.167 --> 02:15.268
Hey.

02:15.301 --> 02:16.269
Where's your
daughter right now?

02:16.302 --> 02:17.270
She's here.

02:17.303 --> 02:18.805
She's safe, and so are you.

02:19.639 --> 02:21.374
He's gonna come for her.

02:21.407 --> 02:22.609
Well, we've got the
place locked down,

02:22.642 --> 02:24.444
I got Vance, and I got a gun.

02:24.477 --> 02:25.778
I'd like to see him try.

02:25.812 --> 02:28.615
Barry said there was
more to it than I know.

02:28.648 --> 02:30.350
I want to know.

02:30.383 --> 02:31.384
Really?

02:33.620 --> 02:35.121
Took you long enough.

02:41.427 --> 02:44.664
Okay, you read the
girl was dead,

02:44.697 --> 02:46.399
and that Scott Riley was
accused of the murder.

02:46.432 --> 02:47.233
Yes.

02:47.267 --> 02:49.402
And you just accepted that?

02:49.435 --> 02:50.904
I had no reason
not to believe it.

02:50.937 --> 02:52.071
Oh, come on, Sheila,

02:52.105 --> 02:54.107
you had over a
million reasons.

02:55.875 --> 02:58.244
You don't think
I don't notice

02:58.278 --> 03:00.613
you flaunting all your
good deeds around town

03:00.647 --> 03:02.015
all the time?

03:02.048 --> 03:03.850
So desperate to prove
that you're good.

03:03.883 --> 03:05.685
I didn't hurt anyone.

03:05.718 --> 03:07.020
Taj:
Neither did I.

03:07.720 --> 03:09.856
She was alive the
last time I saw her.

03:11.591 --> 03:15.728
Cardinal:
Did Ken ever have any
dealings with Sheila Gagne?

03:16.596 --> 03:18.097
Or Barry LeBlanc?

03:19.432 --> 03:22.402
Ken's been in the resources
business for a long time.

03:22.435 --> 03:24.404
This would've been about 1999.

03:24.437 --> 03:26.206
1999, okay.

03:27.707 --> 03:29.909
Cardinal:
How long have you
worked for him?

03:29.943 --> 03:34.914
Since he opened his first
logging company in '93.

03:34.948 --> 03:36.416
He's a good boss.

03:36.449 --> 03:38.952
You ever have any
problems with anyone?

03:38.985 --> 03:40.753
A ex-employee with a grudge,

03:40.787 --> 03:41.955
a competitor?

03:41.988 --> 03:43.990
Well, a little
bit of both, but-

03:46.492 --> 03:47.994
Nothing violent.

03:51.297 --> 03:53.299
Oh, here's something,
Barry LeBlanc.

03:54.500 --> 03:55.735
And Sheila Gagne, too,

03:55.768 --> 03:57.270
they were both paid
as subcontractors

03:57.303 --> 04:00.473
by our forestry division.

04:00.506 --> 04:02.408
Can I, can I see?

04:02.442 --> 04:04.410
Paid quite well, actually.

04:04.444 --> 04:06.412
Subcontracted to do what?

04:06.446 --> 04:07.947
It says consulting.

04:09.449 --> 04:10.450
But, um-

04:14.487 --> 04:16.556
We won a bid to

04:16.589 --> 04:19.492
log a section of the
Aagimaak Forest that year.

04:19.525 --> 04:22.462
It was a big turning
point for the company.

04:22.495 --> 04:24.097
Well I remember
that there was a-

04:24.130 --> 04:27.267
a-a tip about the
upcoming timber rights.

04:27.300 --> 04:28.768
Yeah, Sheila and
Barry both worked

04:28.801 --> 04:30.603
for Watershed Forestry in '99.

04:33.506 --> 04:35.275
(stammering) Oh, I-I-I
didn't know that.

04:36.509 --> 04:37.510
Nelly?

04:38.678 --> 04:42.348
Well, Watershed had all the
local government contracts

04:42.382 --> 04:43.483
at that point.

04:43.516 --> 04:46.719
Well, is it possible
that Barry and Sheila

04:46.753 --> 04:49.522
took that information
and sold it to Ken?

04:49.555 --> 04:52.792
And he paid them
off as consultants.

04:52.825 --> 04:54.827
And made his first fortune.

04:56.562 --> 04:58.531
You would have to ask them.

04:58.564 --> 04:59.832
Yeah.

05:01.334 --> 05:02.869
Barry's dead.

05:03.770 --> 05:06.472
And Sheila and
Ken are missing.

05:06.506 --> 05:08.007
So we're asking you.

05:09.509 --> 05:10.510
Yes.

05:11.778 --> 05:15.481
It is possible that Ken
paid Sheila and Barry

05:15.515 --> 05:20.386
to leak future
logging prospects

05:20.420 --> 05:23.523
using their Watershed access.

05:23.556 --> 05:28.027
So Barry and Sheila share
information illegally,

05:28.061 --> 05:30.063
information that
makes them all rich.

05:31.831 --> 05:33.066
He could.

05:34.834 --> 05:36.069
Thank you.

05:37.370 --> 05:38.604
Can we keep this?

05:41.574 --> 05:47.547
(pulsing suspenseful music)

05:47.580 --> 05:49.549
♪

05:49.582 --> 05:51.884
Radio Announcer:
We're getting call-ins
about rescue activity

05:51.918 --> 05:54.620
around the old
Mead Lake quarry.

05:54.654 --> 05:56.689
Police, fire, and ambulance
vehicles are on the scene,

05:56.723 --> 05:58.725
but no word on
what's going on.

06:00.426 --> 06:02.528
Our sources will not
confirm if this is related

06:02.562 --> 06:04.997
to the disappearance of
resident Josh McNider,

06:05.031 --> 06:08.868
who is the son of local
resources magnate Ken McNider.

06:11.571 --> 06:13.806
We will continue with updates
on this developing story

06:13.840 --> 06:16.409
