12:30.416 --> 12:32.852
♪

12:32.885 --> 12:34.186
Sheila:
Is Mena okay?

12:37.223 --> 12:39.759
Why am I more worried
about her than you are?

12:41.761 --> 12:43.262
Sheila look,

12:45.030 --> 12:46.398
if no one does
anything stupid,

12:46.432 --> 12:49.769
Scott Riley's gonna
get caught, killed.

12:50.269 --> 12:52.238
This'll all be over.

12:52.271 --> 12:53.739
What if he goes
to the police?

12:53.773 --> 12:55.241
Yeah, well,

12:55.274 --> 12:57.209
that really didn't go too well
for him last time, did it?

12:57.243 --> 12:58.644
If I go to my
friend at the OPD-

12:58.677 --> 13:00.312
Whoa, whoa, whoa
stop now, stop-

13:00.346 --> 13:01.614
He will make sure that
we get fair treatment.
-Stop, Sheila, stop.

13:01.647 --> 13:05.184
No, I am telling you,
no more lies.

13:07.086 --> 13:10.156
I cannot carry this anymore.

13:10.189 --> 13:11.490
All right, I'm sorry, okay.

13:12.691 --> 13:14.226
I'm sorry, all right?

13:18.597 --> 13:20.599
I'm not losing my
daughter over this.

13:25.070 --> 13:27.373
Barnhouse:
Not totally frozen
yet like the others.

13:28.507 --> 13:30.042
Hasn't been here long.

13:30.676 --> 13:33.612
This victim was beaten, shot.

13:34.446 --> 13:36.015
It's a different killer.

13:37.416 --> 13:38.918
Barnhouse:
The legs were shattered.

13:39.618 --> 13:41.420
Probably a blunt instrument.

13:44.089 --> 13:45.324
Wrist is broken.

13:46.258 --> 13:47.426
From the blood
patterns up there,

13:47.459 --> 13:50.863
looks like he got
himself to the stairs,

13:50.896 --> 13:52.464
took a tumble.

13:52.498 --> 13:53.766
Barnhouse:
Looks like that to me.

13:55.734 --> 13:57.136
Cause of death?

13:57.169 --> 13:59.705
Possible hypothermia,

13:59.738 --> 14:02.408
combined with the blood
loss from the gunshot.

14:02.441 --> 14:04.443
It was a slow and
painful death.

14:05.411 --> 14:06.912
Thank you, Dr. Barnhouse.

14:11.283 --> 14:13.285
Cardinal:
The other victims,
Adele and Robert,

14:14.253 --> 14:15.487
they were a means to an end,

14:16.422 --> 14:18.224
a way of hurting
their loved ones.

14:19.491 --> 14:21.260
And Barry,

14:21.293 --> 14:22.928
he was an accident,

14:22.962 --> 14:24.496
or he was a suicide.

14:27.499 --> 14:28.534
And I don't think
he took Sheila.

14:28.567 --> 14:30.336
I think she's in hiding.

14:32.338 --> 14:33.906
So what are you saying?

14:35.274 --> 14:37.443
I'm saying I don't think
he meant to kill Ken.

14:38.777 --> 14:42.481
The killer could've found
out that Josh was still alive,

14:42.514 --> 14:45.117
threw off his plan
and made him angry.

14:45.517 --> 14:49.288
Killing Neil Cuthbert would've
thrown off his plan, too.

14:52.157 --> 14:54.393
I don't think he meant to
do any of this himself.

14:57.563 --> 15:02.268
Hey, we just have
to push on through.

15:03.636 --> 15:05.404
Don't let it get personal.

15:06.939 --> 15:08.474
You can't say that to me.

15:12.177 --> 15:13.479
I have to tell Josh.

15:14.413 --> 15:15.681
I'll go with you.

15:16.515 --> 15:17.783
No.

15:19.551 --> 15:21.587
No, I have to do it alone.

15:21.620 --> 15:27.593
(sombre instrumental)

15:27.626 --> 15:30.629
♪

15:32.998 --> 15:34.166
(distant train whistle)

15:44.376 --> 15:45.678
Lise.

15:48.914 --> 15:50.749
Have you found my father?

15:50.783 --> 15:56.755
(sombre instrumental)

15:56.789 --> 15:59.658
♪

15:59.692 --> 16:00.693
He's dead.

16:05.731 --> 16:07.032
I'm sorry.

16:10.869 --> 16:12.338
I thought you were
good at this,

16:12.371 --> 16:13.906
you and your partner.

16:20.512 --> 16:21.880
My father, Lise-

16:24.917 --> 16:26.185
Did he-

16:27.619 --> 16:28.921
Did he suffer?

16:33.425 --> 16:34.727
I'm afraid he did.

16:42.768 --> 16:46.538
Josh, is there anything you
remember about your father?

16:46.572 --> 16:48.607
Anything that might
help us find out

16:48.640 --> 16:49.942
who would want to
hurt him like this?

16:49.975 --> 16:51.543
Josh:
No, Lise, no.

16:54.413 --> 16:56.715
And you should leave
us alone, please.

16:58.017 --> 16:59.685
(Lise sighs)

16:59.718 --> 17:00.953
I'm sorry.

17:05.224 --> 17:11.196
(soft instrumental)

