31:48.773 --> 31:50.475
but, um, Commanda
is in the boardroom

31:50.508 --> 31:53.311
with background material on
the Rebecca Bailey case.

31:57.148 --> 31:58.516
How was Toronto?

31:59.651 --> 32:00.919
Good.
-It was good.

32:06.090 --> 32:09.661
I pulled everything I could
on the Rebecca Bailey murder.

32:09.694 --> 32:13.131
This is the original arrest
interview with Scott Riley

32:13.164 --> 32:14.632
from 1999.

32:14.666 --> 32:15.633
Were you involved in the case?

32:15.667 --> 32:16.634
Commanda:
I was in Timmins.

32:16.668 --> 32:18.803
Bob McKinley was
the investigator.

32:18.836 --> 32:22.006
I never met
the guy, but uh-

32:22.040 --> 32:23.541
Well, you'll get the idea.

32:26.411 --> 32:28.713
McKinley:
So can you please
tell me again

32:28.746 --> 32:30.682
what you and
Rebecca Bailey were doing

32:30.715 --> 32:33.718
in a remote section of
the Aagimaak Forest?

32:33.751 --> 32:36.587
Young Scott:
We, looking for
Peregrine Falcon.

32:37.722 --> 32:38.690
It's endangered.

32:38.723 --> 32:39.857
McKinley:
Oh.

32:39.891 --> 32:41.693
So, did you find them?

32:41.726 --> 32:42.527
Young Scott:
No.

32:42.560 --> 32:43.528
McKinley:
Ah.

32:43.561 --> 32:44.862
Young Scott:
We heard shooting, so-

32:44.896 --> 32:46.731
(ominous instrumental)

32:46.764 --> 32:48.333
Young Scott:
We went to see what it was.

32:48.933 --> 32:50.501
And there was
blood in the snow.

32:51.602 --> 32:53.137
On a bloody feather.

32:53.171 --> 32:56.074
McKinley:
They were killing
your birds, huh?

32:56.107 --> 32:57.875
Those 'parka people'
of yours.

32:57.909 --> 32:59.610
Young Scott:
Stop calling them that.

32:59.644 --> 33:01.679
McKinley:
That's what you
called 'em before.

33:01.713 --> 33:03.514
And these parka people
were the ones

33:03.548 --> 33:05.683
who assaulted Rebecca,
you said, right?

33:05.717 --> 33:06.784
Yes.

33:06.818 --> 33:09.687
Ah, and, now the sexual
assault was them too-

33:09.721 --> 33:10.989
Young Scott:
I told you,

33:11.022 --> 33:12.557
I did not rape her.

33:14.892 --> 33:18.696
McKinley:
Why do you think these
people were shooting falcons?

33:19.597 --> 33:20.898
What?

33:21.532 --> 33:23.501
Well we went where you
said and there were no,

33:23.534 --> 33:25.003
there were no feathers,

33:25.036 --> 33:26.571
no dead birds.

33:27.538 --> 33:28.706
My question is,

33:28.740 --> 33:31.442
is why kill them
at all, hm?

33:31.476 --> 33:34.045
If endangered birds
are nesting there,

33:34.078 --> 33:35.713
the area is protected,

33:35.747 --> 33:36.948
so if they wanted to log,

33:36.981 --> 33:38.483
then killing them would be-

33:39.384 --> 33:40.752
We had to confront
them, okay.

33:40.785 --> 33:41.919
But I never touched them.

33:41.953 --> 33:44.022
They hit first.

33:44.055 --> 33:45.757
You can't describe
these people?

33:45.790 --> 33:46.791
Young Scott:
Well they had their-

33:47.625 --> 33:50.661
They had their hoods up,
couldn't see their faces.

33:51.963 --> 33:54.699
Look, one might've
been a woman,

33:54.732 --> 33:57.702
but she left when
we got there.

33:57.735 --> 33:59.037
McKinley:
Mm hm.

33:59.070 --> 34:01.672
Young Scott:
Look, we started
pushing, okay,

34:01.706 --> 34:04.709
and one of them tried to hit
me with the butt of his rifle.

34:06.377 --> 34:08.713
It was a white guy, older.

34:08.746 --> 34:10.715
(ominous instrumental)

34:10.748 --> 34:12.250
I dodged him, but-

34:14.986 --> 34:16.487
Rebecca, he uh-

34:16.754 --> 34:18.022
He hit her, okay.

34:18.056 --> 34:19.357
I mean, knocked her down.

34:19.390 --> 34:23.628
So I bent down to help
her and I just saw the guy

34:23.661 --> 34:25.396
who hit her talk to
one of the others,

34:25.430 --> 34:27.231
and then that guy took off.

34:29.801 --> 34:30.768
God.

34:30.802 --> 34:31.602
How many people
were there there?

34:31.636 --> 34:33.037
Four!

34:33.071 --> 34:36.040
Look, I keep telling you four.

34:36.074 --> 34:38.176
McKinley:
So you dragged
this bleeding girl

34:38.209 --> 34:39.710
into the middle of nowhere?

34:40.678 --> 34:44.215
Young Scott:
I was holding her up,
trying to help her.

34:44.816 --> 34:47.251
I got her to the snowmobile,
but the keys were gone.

34:47.285 --> 34:49.754
That guy who took off,
he must've taken them.

34:49.787 --> 34:52.457
McKinley:
So this guy ran
to your camp,

34:52.490 --> 34:54.625
took the keys to your
snow machine and vanished,

34:54.659 --> 34:56.627
all before you got there?

34:56.661 --> 34:58.796
She was bleeding, okay?

34:58.830 --> 35:01.432
I had to get her out,
so we started walking.

35:01.466 --> 35:03.935
Ah, but you said that
she couldn't walk, hm?

35:03.968 --> 35:05.203
So you dragged
her for a while.

35:05.236 --> 35:08.005
And then when you got
tired you left her?

35:09.640 --> 35:10.808
Young Scott:
I told you,

35:10.842 --> 35:12.844
I left her to get help.

35:12.877 --> 35:14.645
Okay, I didn't drag her.

35:14.679 --> 35:15.813
I left her to get help!

35:15.847 --> 35:18.116
I left her to get help!

35:20.218 --> 35:22.086
Well, Detective,
uh, McKinley

35:22.120 --> 35:24.288
had his mind made up
about Scott Riley.

35:24.322 --> 35:25.523
Yeah, I went
through his notes.

35:25.556 --> 35:27.825
He had Scott pegged
as an eco-terrorist,

35:27.859 --> 35:29.827
history of aggression.

35:29.861 --> 35:31.462
Priors?

35:31.496 --> 35:32.630
Commanda:
He was arrested at two
environmental rallies

35:32.663 --> 35:34.098
in Toronto the year before,

35:34.132 --> 35:35.333
but it was nothing.

35:35.366 --> 35:37.101
Okay, any other suspects?

35:37.135 --> 35:40.004
Well, McKinley talked to a
couple of local sex offenders,

35:40.037 --> 35:43.074
but no record of him looking
for the four people in parkas.

35:43.107 --> 35:44.375
Tunnel vision.

35:45.109 --> 35:47.245
(sighs) Rebecca had
a blow to the head,

35:47.278 --> 35:50.348
bruising that could've come
from a fall in the woods.

35:50.381 --> 35:52.717
The only evidence to
suggest sexual assault

35:52.750 --> 35:55.386
was Riley's DNA and the fact
that she was found half-naked.

35:55.419 --> 35:56.621
If she was hypothermic,

35:56.654 --> 35:58.189
I mean, she might
well have stripped off

35:58.222 --> 35:59.991
like Robert Quillen.

36:00.024 --> 36:02.193
And maybe the sex
was consensual,

36:02.226 --> 36:03.461
like Riley claims.

36:03.494 --> 36:07.632
So he's convicted
for rape and murder

36:07.665 --> 36:09.100
and loses everything:

36:09.133 --> 36:10.334
the woman he loves,

36:10.368 --> 36:11.636
his parents,

36:11.669 --> 36:13.104
twenty years of his life.

36:13.137 --> 36:14.772
That would explain the rage.

36:14.805 --> 36:16.541
Twenty years for
it to build up.

36:16.574 --> 36:18.576
Twenty years to
plan his revenge.

36:20.378 --> 36:21.979
Sheila Gagne,

36:22.013 --> 36:23.881
Ken McNider,

36:23.915 --> 36:25.750
Barry LeBlanc.

36:25.783 --> 36:27.752
Those were his parka people.

36:27.785 --> 36:31.389
He wants them to pay
for Rebecca's death,

36:31.422 --> 36:32.990
and he wants them
to suffer too.

36:33.024 --> 36:34.559
That's three.

36:35.393 --> 36:37.895
So who's the fourth
and how do we find them?

36:37.929 --> 36:40.097
Sheila phoned Ken,
we're pretty sure of that,

36:40.131 --> 36:44.101
and the warrant gets us access
to her cell phone records.

36:44.135 --> 36:46.504
Maybe Sheila phoned
this fourth person,

